WEBVTT

01:38.683 --> 01:41.478
[GROWLS]

01:41.644 --> 01:44.189
[BAA]

01:47.108 --> 01:48.318
[BARKS]

01:48.485 --> 01:50.195
[BAA]

02:56.594 --> 02:57.595
UH!

02:57.762 --> 02:58.680
NOT TOO GOOD.

02:58.847 --> 02:59.973
BETTER THAN YOU.

03:07.647 --> 03:08.898
NOT AS FAR.

03:09.065 --> 03:10.275
I KNOW.

03:10.441 --> 03:11.568
MA, COME
AND JUMP!

03:11.734 --> 03:14.404
DON'T BE SILLY.
I GOT WORK
TO GET DONE.

03:14.571 --> 03:15.363
PLEASE?

03:15.530 --> 03:16.614
JUST FOR A MINUTE.

03:16.781 --> 03:18.575
I HAVEN'T GOT TIME
FOR SUCH FOOLISHNESS.

03:18.741 --> 03:20.869
HOW COME IT'S NOT FOOLISHNESS
WHEN WE DO IT?

03:21.035 --> 03:22.954
BECAUSE
YOU'RE CHILDREN,
AND I'M AN ADULT.

03:23.121 --> 03:24.163
WHEN A CHILD DOES
SOME--

03:24.330 --> 03:25.373
THEN GROWNUPS SAY,

03:25.540 --> 03:27.000
"IT'S SO EASY,
A CHILD CAN DO IT."

03:27.166 --> 03:29.669
I THINK THEY SAY IT
JUST SO THEY DON'T
HAVE TO TRY

03:29.836 --> 03:31.129
THE STUFF KIDS CAN DO.

03:31.296 --> 03:34.507
NOW, JUST A MINUTE,
YOUNG LADY.

03:34.674 --> 03:36.509
ARE YOU SAYING
THAT I CAN'T JUMP
AS FAR AS YOU CAN?

03:36.676 --> 03:41.014
NO, MA'AM, BUT MY PA
SAYS THAT SAYING
YOU CAN DO SOMETHING

03:41.180 --> 03:43.057
AND DOING IT ARE
TWO DIFFERENT THINGS.

03:47.604 --> 03:51.774
ALL RIGHT, THEN...
I'LL JUST SHOW YOU.

03:51.941 --> 03:54.027
HA HA HA!

03:59.157 --> 04:01.701
THIS IS GOING TO BE
GOOD. HA HA HA!

04:02.911 --> 04:04.495
[DOG BARKING]

04:06.247 --> 04:07.582
Laura: HI, BANDIT!

04:07.749 --> 04:10.460
BANDIT, YOU SHOWED UP
JUST IN THE NICK OF TIME.

04:10.627 --> 04:11.419
HEY, BOY.

04:11.586 --> 04:13.713
HELLO, BOY.
YOU COME TO GET ME?

04:13.880 --> 04:15.214
DID YOU COME
TO GET ME?

04:15.381 --> 04:16.674
HE KNOWS THE WAY
REAL GOOD.

04:16.841 --> 04:18.468
HE GOES BACK
AND FORTH A LOT.

04:18.635 --> 04:19.719
YEAH!

04:19.886 --> 04:21.262
WELL, I GUESS
I GOT TO GO.
SEE YA, ANDY!

04:21.429 --> 04:22.305
BYE, MRS. GARVEY.

04:22.472 --> 04:23.264
BYE.

04:23.431 --> 04:24.641
READY TO JUMP?

04:24.807 --> 04:26.643
I'D LOVE TO, ANDY,
BUT I'VE GOT
WORK TO DO.

04:26.809 --> 04:27.852
OH, MA.

04:28.019 --> 04:29.604
NO "OH, MA" WITH ME!

04:29.771 --> 04:31.856
YOU GET IN
THAT HOUSE AND DO
YOUR HOMEWORK, TOO.

04:32.023 --> 04:34.067
YES, MA'AM.

05:00.259 --> 05:02.345
OH!

05:02.512 --> 05:04.180
HA HA HA!

05:04.347 --> 05:05.807
NOT TOO GOOD.

05:05.974 --> 05:06.975
NEVER MIND!

05:07.141 --> 05:08.851
YOU GET
IN THERE AND DO
YOUR HOMEWORK.

05:09.018 --> 05:10.603
HA HA HA!

05:12.522 --> 05:14.107
OH!

05:29.872 --> 05:31.082
YOU ABOUT READY, PA?

05:31.249 --> 05:33.876
YEAH, IF YOUR MOTHER
EVER GETS READY.
LOOK OUT, DOG!

05:34.043 --> 05:35.128
CAROLINE!

05:35.294 --> 05:36.629
COMING!

05:36.796 --> 05:39.757
NOW, MARY, LET'S
JUST GO OVER THAT
ONE MORE TIME.

05:39.924 --> 05:41.676
WE'VE BEEN OVER IT
10 TIMES, MA.

05:41.843 --> 05:44.095
I KNOW, DEAR,
BUT I CAN'T HELP
BUT BE CONCERNED.

05:44.262 --> 05:46.764
NOW, I WANT YOU
TO REMEMBER TO KEEP
A CLOSE WATCH

05:46.931 --> 05:47.974
ON THAT SORE
ON CARRIE'S LEG--

05:48.141 --> 05:49.642
AND MAKE SURE LAURA
DOES HER STUDYING

05:49.809 --> 05:51.811
AND SEE THAT THE WOOD
STOVE STAYS LIT
AND THAT THE--

05:51.978 --> 05:53.187
YES, I'M CONVINCED!

05:53.354 --> 05:55.064
YOU REALLY ARE
READY FOR THIS.

05:55.231 --> 05:56.107
Charles: CAROLINE!

05:56.274 --> 05:57.692
COMING!

05:57.859 --> 05:59.569
OH, BE A GOOD GIRL.

06:02.030 --> 06:04.198
BYE, SWEETHEART.

06:04.365 --> 06:06.159
OH, LAURA, NOW,
REMEMBER TO MIND
YOUR SISTER.

06:06.325 --> 06:07.285
I WILL.

06:07.452 --> 06:09.162
Charles: CAROLINE,
I WANT TO GO TODAY!

06:09.328 --> 06:10.371
COMING, CHARLES!

06:10.538 --> 06:11.873
OH!

06:14.917 --> 06:16.753
I COULD HAVE BEEN TO
TWIN FALLS AND BACK

06:16.919 --> 06:18.546
BY THE TIME YOU TWO
FINISHED SAYING GOOD-BYE.

06:18.713 --> 06:19.797
I'M SORRY.

06:19.964 --> 06:21.257
WE'RE ONLY GOING TO BE
GONE FOR TWO DAYS.

06:21.424 --> 06:22.759
I'M SURE THEY'RE
GOING TO SURVIVE.

06:22.925 --> 06:24.260
DON'T WORRY, MA.
WE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

06:24.427 --> 06:26.846
SEE WHAT I MEAN?
WE'LL SEE YOU SOON!

06:27.013 --> 06:27.889
BYE!

06:28.056 --> 06:28.931
TAKE CARE, NOW.

06:29.098 --> 06:29.849
WE WILL!

06:30.016 --> 06:30.933
Mary: HAVE
A GOOD TRIP!

06:31.100 --> 06:31.851
WE WILL!

06:32.018 --> 06:33.269
THANK YOU.
BYE-BYE!

06:34.479 --> 06:36.439
Laura:
BYE-BYE, MA!

06:36.606 --> 06:37.899
BYE, PA!

06:38.066 --> 06:39.776
BYE, HONEY!

06:48.076 --> 06:49.243
I DIDN'T REALIZE

06:49.410 --> 06:51.704
THERE WERE SO MANY
DIFFERENT KIND OF PANS.

06:51.871 --> 06:53.873
I DO WISH YOU WOULD
DECIDE, MR. GARVEY.

06:54.040 --> 06:55.708
I DO HAVE OTHER
WORK TO TEND TO.

06:55.875 --> 06:59.837
WELL, I'M THINKING.
I'M ABOUT READY
TO MAKE UP MY MIND.

07:00.004 --> 07:02.882
WELL, I'M STILL
RECOMMENDING
THIS ONE.

07:03.049 --> 07:05.927
IT SEEMS A MITE
EXPENSIVE TO ME,
MA'AM.

07:06.094 --> 07:07.929
QUALITY DOESN'T COME
CHEAP, MR. GARVEY.

07:08.096 --> 07:10.556
NOW, LOOK
AT THE WORKMANSHIP
OF THIS.

07:10.723 --> 07:12.475
OH, YOU CAN EVEN
SEE MY REFLECTION
IN IT.

07:12.642 --> 07:14.977
WELL, I DON'T
REALLY NEED ONE
TO LOOK IN, MA'AM.

07:15.144 --> 07:16.979
I JUST NEED ONE
TO COOK IN.

07:17.146 --> 07:18.898
I THINK I'M GONNA
TAKE THIS ONE,

07:19.065 --> 07:21.067
AND WOULD YOU THROW IN
SOME CHEWING TOBACCO FOR ME?

07:21.234 --> 07:22.693
CERTAINLY.

07:22.860 --> 07:24.362
[BELLS ON DOOR RING]

07:33.246 --> 07:34.914
JUDD.

07:35.081 --> 07:36.749
MRS. OLESON,
I NEED SOME TRAPS.

07:36.916 --> 07:39.919
BE RIGHT
WITH YOU.
64 CENTS.

07:40.086 --> 07:41.921
WHAT YOU--
WHAT YOU
TRAPPING?

07:42.088 --> 07:43.923
I DON'T RECOLLECT
ADDRESSING YOU.

07:44.090 --> 07:46.884
WOLF TRAPS--YOU GOT
ANY, MRS. OLESON?

07:47.051 --> 07:48.427
UH, YES, WE
HAVE QUITE
A FEW--

07:48.594 --> 07:49.637
DIFFERENT
KINDS.

07:49.804 --> 07:50.930
I WANT THE BEST.

07:51.097 --> 07:52.515
AIN'T NO WOLVES
HEREABOUTS.

07:52.682 --> 07:55.935
I GOT TWO DEAD SHEEP
THAT SAY DIFFERENT.

07:57.103 --> 07:58.938
BEST BE CAREFUL
WITH THEM TRAPS.

07:59.105 --> 08:00.523
THEY CAN BE
AWFUL DANGEROUS.

08:00.690 --> 08:02.984
I'LL LOOK AFTER
MY OWN HIDE,
THANK YOU.

08:03.151 --> 08:05.027
YOU STICK
TO WORRYING
ABOUT YOUR'N.

08:10.283 --> 08:14.954
WELL, IT'S ABOUT TIME
SOMEONE SAID SOMETHING
TO HIM--STOOD UP TO HIM!

08:15.121 --> 08:18.624
THE WAY HE STRUTS
AROUND THIS TOWN.
TSK TSK TSK!

08:18.791 --> 08:20.626
MRS. OLESON,
I'D LIKE TO SEE
THEM TRAPS.

08:20.793 --> 08:22.420
OH, YES, SIR.
THEY'RE THIS WAY.

08:25.256 --> 08:27.425
HERE YOU ARE--
ALL KINDS.

08:33.139 --> 08:35.558
I'VE HEARD TALK THAT
YOU AND MR. GARVEY

08:35.725 --> 08:38.603
HAD QUITE A BIT
OF TROUBLE BACK
IN KANSAS.

08:38.769 --> 08:40.646
'TWEREN'T
NO TROUBLE.

08:40.813 --> 08:42.523
COME ON NOW,
MR. LARABEE.

08:42.690 --> 08:45.651
I UNDERSTAND
THAT HE STOLE
SOME FURS FROM YOU.

08:45.818 --> 08:47.028
MAYBE.
I'LL TAKE THESE.

08:47.195 --> 08:48.946
PUT THEM
ON MY ACCOUNT.

08:49.113 --> 08:50.114
OH, YES.

08:50.281 --> 08:51.073
MORNING.

08:51.240 --> 08:52.992
OH, GOOD MORNING.

08:57.914 --> 08:59.665
POOR MAN.

08:59.832 --> 09:01.500
GARVEY WAS IN HERE
EARLIER.

09:01.667 --> 09:05.004
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN
THE LOOK OF ANGER
ON LARABEE'S FACE.

09:05.171 --> 09:07.715
OH, THOSE TWO
STILL CAN'T GET
ALONG, HUH?

09:07.882 --> 09:09.759
WELL, I'M NOT
SURPRISED.

09:09.926 --> 09:11.719
GARVEY STOLE
HIS FURS.

09:11.886 --> 09:13.721
NOW, HOLD ON NOW.
WAIT A MINUTE.

09:13.888 --> 09:15.681
I THINK YOU GOT
THAT BACKWARDS.

09:15.848 --> 09:17.350
THE WAY I HEARD
THE STORY,

09:17.516 --> 09:19.602
IF THERE'S ANYBODY
THAT'S GOT ANY
COMPLAINTS,

09:19.769 --> 09:21.270
IT'S GARVEY.
HE'S THE ONE THAT
WAS FALSELY ACCUSED.

09:21.437 --> 09:23.731
MR. LARABEE SAID
THAT HE STOLE
THE FURS,

09:23.898 --> 09:25.733
AND THAT'S WHAT
HE TOLD THE JUDGE.

09:25.900 --> 09:27.526
THEY CAUGHT
THE CROOK
RED-HANDED!

09:27.693 --> 09:30.613
WITH THE FURS!
THERE WAS NO
QUESTION AFTER THAT.

09:30.780 --> 09:33.366
WELL, MR. LARABEE
STILL HAD HIS DOUBTS.

09:33.532 --> 09:35.826
THE ONLY THING
THAT LARABEE'S GOT

09:35.993 --> 09:37.703
IS A BAD CASE
OF BEING HUMILIATED

09:37.870 --> 09:39.121
IN FRONT
OF THAT WHOLE TOWN.

09:39.288 --> 09:40.915
THAT'S WHAT
HE WON'T FORGIVE
GARVEY FOR.

09:42.250 --> 09:45.211
WELL, I DON'T CARE.
I STILL DON'T
TRUST GARVEY.

09:46.379 --> 09:48.631
FOR HEAVEN'S SAKES,
WHY NOT?

09:49.799 --> 09:52.218
WELL...BECAUSE
HE CHEWS TOBACCO,

09:52.385 --> 09:54.512
AND HE SPITS!
THAT'S WHY.

09:55.930 --> 09:59.642
OH, WELL, WHY
DIDN'T YOU SAY THAT
IN THE FIRST PLACE?

09:59.809 --> 10:02.436
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU HAD A GOOD REASON.

10:09.151 --> 10:11.988
THAT BASKET
ISN'T GETTING
ANY FULLER.

10:12.154 --> 10:13.739
I KNOW, BUT I AM.

10:13.906 --> 10:15.032
YOU GOT TO STOP
EATING THEM.

10:15.199 --> 10:16.325
YOUR MOM WANTS
TO MAKE SOME PIES.

10:16.492 --> 10:17.952
JUST A FEW MORE.

10:18.119 --> 10:19.287
OK, 3 MORE EACH.

10:19.453 --> 10:21.122
HOW ABOUT 5 MORE?

10:21.289 --> 10:22.415
[BANDIT BARKS]

10:22.581 --> 10:25.126
I WONDER WHAT
BANDIT'S BARKING AT.

10:25.293 --> 10:26.419
I DON'T KNOW.

10:26.585 --> 10:29.422
HE SOUNDS AWFUL
ANGRY. COME ON!

10:30.715 --> 10:32.425
[BARKING CONTINUES]

10:43.311 --> 10:44.603
ANDY, LOOK.

10:44.770 --> 10:46.814
[WHIMPERING]

10:49.275 --> 10:51.819
BANDIT, BE QUIET.
STAY HERE.

10:57.616 --> 11:00.619
POOR OLD DOG...
HE'S HURT BAD.

11:00.786 --> 11:03.372
HE'S SO PRETTY.

11:03.539 --> 11:05.916
MAYBE WE CAN
GET HIM FREE.

11:06.083 --> 11:08.794
I DON'T KNOW.
THAT TRAP LOOKS
AWFUL BIG.

11:08.961 --> 11:11.964
THAT'S A GOOD BOY.
I'M NOT GOING TO
HURT YOU.

11:12.131 --> 11:13.215
BE CAREFUL.

11:13.382 --> 11:16.260
IT'S OK. HE'S JUST
SCARED IS ALL.

11:16.427 --> 11:18.346
COME ON, LAURA.
I NEED YOUR HELP.

11:18.512 --> 11:20.014
OK, TAKE THAT SIDE.

11:20.181 --> 11:20.973
OK.

11:21.140 --> 11:22.016
OK, READY?

11:22.183 --> 11:23.184
READY.

11:23.351 --> 11:24.602
Andy: PUSH!

11:24.769 --> 11:26.145
[WHIMPERING]

11:26.312 --> 11:29.231
UH! THERE.
GET HIS FOOT OUT.

11:29.398 --> 11:30.983
QUICK!

11:31.150 --> 11:32.985
WE DID IT!

11:33.152 --> 11:34.945
NOW WHAT
DO WE DO?

11:35.112 --> 11:37.281
HIS LEG LOOKS
AWFUL BAD.

11:38.324 --> 11:39.325
WHERE'S HE GOING?

11:39.492 --> 11:41.327
WE'VE GOT TO
FIX HIS LEG.

11:41.494 --> 11:43.412
LET'S FOLLOW HIM.

11:58.552 --> 12:00.012
[WHIMPERING]

12:00.179 --> 12:01.222
OH, ANDY, LOOK!

12:01.389 --> 12:03.516
HE'S A SHE!

12:03.682 --> 12:06.852
YEAH, AND SHE'S HURT
TOO BAD TO TAKE CARE
OF HER PUPS.

12:07.019 --> 12:08.104
WHAT'S A DOG DOING

12:08.270 --> 12:10.147
ALL THE WAY OUT HERE
IN THE WOODS ANYWAY?

12:10.314 --> 12:12.066
I DON'T KNOW.
SHE MUST BE LOST.

12:12.233 --> 12:14.151
WE'LL HAVE TO
TAKE HER HOME
AND FIX HER FOOT.

12:14.318 --> 12:17.196
WE CAN'T LEAVE
THE PUPS HERE
ALL ALONE.

12:17.363 --> 12:18.864
WE'VE GOT TO
TAKE THEM ALL.

12:19.031 --> 12:20.783
MY MA AND PA
ARE AWAY.

12:20.950 --> 12:23.411
I DON'T KNOW
IF MARY WILL LET ME
KEEP THEM.

12:23.577 --> 12:24.995
I'LL TAKE THEM HOME.

12:25.162 --> 12:26.956
COME ON.
WE'LL GET MY CART.

12:29.875 --> 12:31.085
GUESS WHAT
ME AND ANDY FOUND--

12:31.252 --> 12:32.545
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN,
YOUNG LADY?
YOU'RE LATE!

12:32.711 --> 12:33.587
HUH?

12:33.754 --> 12:35.089
I ASKED YOU
WHERE YOU'VE BEEN.

12:35.256 --> 12:36.882
WELL, I WAS TRYING
TO TELL YOU.
ME AND ANDREW--

12:37.049 --> 12:38.717
THE FACT IS,
YOU'RE LATE!

12:38.884 --> 12:41.053
I KNOW I'M LATE.
THAT'S WHY I'M TRYING
TO TELL YOU--

12:41.220 --> 12:42.555
I DON'T WANT
TO DISCUSS IT!

12:42.721 --> 12:44.056
YOU'RE JUST GOING TO
HAVE TO MIND ME,

12:44.223 --> 12:45.558
WHETHER YOU LIKE IT
OR NOT!

12:45.724 --> 12:47.601
DON'T YOU
WANT TO EVEN KNOW
WHAT WE FOUND?

12:47.768 --> 12:49.979
I DON'T HAVE TIME
RIGHT NOW.

13:06.454 --> 13:07.246
HEY, ANDREW.

13:07.413 --> 13:08.789
WHAT YOU GOT
AHOLD OF NOW?

13:08.956 --> 13:11.917
JUST A DOG, PA,
WITH HER BABIES.
SHE'S HURT.

13:12.084 --> 13:13.210
WHERE'D YOU GET HER?

13:13.377 --> 13:15.671
DOWN BY THE CREEK.
SHE WAS CAUGHT
IN A TRAP.

13:15.838 --> 13:17.214
ME AND LAURA
GOT HER OUT.

13:17.381 --> 13:19.425
ISN'T SHE
A PRETTY DOG, PA?

13:19.592 --> 13:21.969
[GROWLING SOFTLY]

13:22.136 --> 13:23.179
LORD HAVE MERCY, SON,

13:23.345 --> 13:25.014
THEM AIN'T DOGS,
THEY'S WOLVES!

13:25.181 --> 13:26.390
WOLVES?

13:26.557 --> 13:28.225
WOLVES, ANDREW.
WE CAN'T KEEP THEM
AROUND HERE.

13:28.392 --> 13:31.103
YOU'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO TAKE THEM BACK
WHERE YOU FOUND THEM.

13:31.270 --> 13:32.229
BUT, PA...

13:32.396 --> 13:35.024
LOOK AT HOW BAD
SHE'S HURT.

13:35.191 --> 13:36.317
I KNOW,

13:36.484 --> 13:38.444
BUT THERE AIN'T NOTHIN'
WE CAN DO FOR HER.

13:38.611 --> 13:39.862
SHE DON'T BELONG HERE.

13:40.029 --> 13:41.822
WHY NOT?
WHAT'S WRONG
WITH A WOLF?

13:41.989 --> 13:45.534
WELL, IT AIN'T
THAT THERE'S SOMETHING
WRONG WITH THEM, IT'S--

13:45.701 --> 13:46.952
PA?

13:47.119 --> 13:48.204
YEAH?

13:48.370 --> 13:49.455
DON'T YOU THINK

13:49.622 --> 13:51.290
THAT SHE'S ONE
OF GOD'S CREATURES?

13:51.457 --> 13:55.002
WELL...YEAH,
I THINK SO,

13:55.169 --> 13:56.962
BUT THERE'S
MORE TO IT THAN THAT.

13:57.129 --> 13:58.339
DON'T YOU ALWAYS SAY

13:58.506 --> 14:00.966
WE GOT TO
TAKE GOOD CARE
OF GOD'S CREATURES

14:01.133 --> 14:03.802
AND THAT HE MADE
EVERY ONE FOR A VERY
SPECIAL REASON

14:03.969 --> 14:06.138
AND THAT HE LOVES
THEM ALL THE SAME?

14:07.431 --> 14:12.144
YEAH, I...
I GUESS I DID SAY
SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

14:14.396 --> 14:17.149
ALL RIGHT, I'LL GO IN
AND SEE DOC BAKER

14:17.316 --> 14:20.361
AND SEE IF HE CAN
COME OUT AND HAVE A LOOK
AT HER IN THE MORNING.

14:20.528 --> 14:21.987
THANKS, PA!

14:22.154 --> 14:23.656
[PUPS WHIMPERING]

14:24.990 --> 14:26.200
IT'S OK.

14:26.367 --> 14:29.286
DOC BAKER'S GOING TO
FIX YOUR MAMA UP
REAL NICE.

14:57.815 --> 15:00.776
[DOGS BARKING LOUDLY]

15:02.611 --> 15:04.488
[COW MOOS]

15:23.549 --> 15:25.426
LAURA,
PUT THAT LIGHT OUT.

15:25.593 --> 15:27.219
I'M DOING HOMEWORK.

15:27.386 --> 15:29.847
I DON'T CARE!
YOU SHOULD HAVE BEEN
FINISHED AN HOUR AGO.

15:30.014 --> 15:31.932
WELL, I'M NOT.

15:34.435 --> 15:37.396
LOOK, I DID
ALL THE COOKING
AND THE CLEANING

15:37.563 --> 15:40.274
AND MY HOMEWORK,
AND I MANAGED
TO FINISH.

15:40.441 --> 15:43.027
THAT'S 'CAUSE
YOU'RE PERFECT.

15:43.193 --> 15:45.446
I'VE GOT A BIG DAY
TOMORROW.

15:45.613 --> 15:48.198
NOW PUT OUT
THE LIGHT.

15:48.365 --> 15:50.743
YES, MA'AM.

16:04.423 --> 16:07.593
I TOLD YOU TO
PUT OUT THE LIGHT.

16:07.760 --> 16:10.429
I DID.
THAT'S THE MOON.

16:10.596 --> 16:13.223
YOU CAN MAKE ME DO
ANYTHING YOU WANT,

16:13.390 --> 16:15.684
BUT YOU CAN'T STOP
THE MOON FROM SHINING.

16:15.851 --> 16:18.812
ONLY GOD CAN DO THAT.

16:45.964 --> 16:48.050
NOT YOU, TOO.

16:52.888 --> 16:54.973
SHE'LL REALLY
GET BETTER?

16:55.140 --> 16:56.475
I THINK SO, ANDREW.

16:56.642 --> 16:59.311
SHE'S HURT BAD,
BUT I'M SURE
SHE'LL HEAL.

16:59.478 --> 17:00.562
HOW'S IT GOING, DOC?

17:00.729 --> 17:01.647
FINE.

17:01.814 --> 17:03.107
HE SAYS
SHE'LL GET BETTER.

17:03.273 --> 17:06.110
OH, GOOD.
DOC, YOU WANT TO
HELP ME WITH THIS?

17:06.276 --> 17:07.695
SURE THING.

17:10.739 --> 17:12.616
Andy: WHAT ARE YOU
DOING THAT FOR?

17:12.783 --> 17:13.951
SHE WON'T HURT
ANYBODY.

17:14.118 --> 17:15.494
WELL, I KNOW, SON,

17:15.661 --> 17:17.496
BUT I'M JUST
MAKING SURE.

17:17.663 --> 17:19.039
YOUR PA'S RIGHT, ANDREW.

17:19.206 --> 17:22.334
THIS WOLF'S A WILD ANIMAL,
AND SHE'S HURT BAD.

17:22.501 --> 17:24.878
YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT
SHE'S GOING TO GET IT
INTO HER HEAD TO DO.

17:25.045 --> 17:26.505
BESIDES, AN OUNCE
OF PREVENTION...

17:26.672 --> 17:28.090
IS WORTH
A POUND OF CURE.

17:28.257 --> 17:29.883
THAT'S WHAT MISS BEADLE
ALWAYS SAYS.

17:30.050 --> 17:31.927
SPEAKING OF WHICH,
ISN'T IT ABOUT TIME

17:32.094 --> 17:33.303
YOU WERE HEADED OFF
FOR SCHOOL?

17:33.470 --> 17:34.221
I GUESS.

17:34.388 --> 17:35.973
GUESS NOTHING.
NOW, GET!

17:36.140 --> 17:37.474
BYE, DOC BAKER.
THANKS!

17:37.641 --> 17:38.600
ANDREW.

17:38.767 --> 17:39.768
YEAH, PA?

17:39.935 --> 17:41.186
WHO KNOWS
ABOUT THIS?

17:41.353 --> 17:42.646
JUST US
AND LAURA.

17:42.813 --> 17:45.315
THINK WE BEST
KEEP IT THAT WAY
FOR A WHILE, HUH?

17:45.482 --> 17:48.026
SURE, PA, WHATEVER
YOU SAY. SEE YA!

17:48.193 --> 17:49.570
SEE YA, SON.

17:52.531 --> 17:54.366
SOUNDS LIKE ANDREW
MIGHT BE THINKING

17:54.533 --> 17:55.868
HE'S GOT HIMSELF
A NEW PET.

17:56.034 --> 17:58.328
YEAH, I'M AFRAID
HE'S GETTING
AWFUL ATTACHED.

17:58.495 --> 18:00.706
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT
THINKING OF LETTING
HIM KEEP IT.

18:00.873 --> 18:04.042
NO, NO, NO.
I'LL BE TALKING TO HIM
SOON ENOUGH, DOC.

18:04.209 --> 18:07.588
I GOT TO SHUT IT OFF
BEFORE IT GOES TOO FAR.

18:07.755 --> 18:08.881
WELL, GOOD LUCK.

18:09.047 --> 18:11.508
SAY, DOC, COULD YOU
DO ME A FAVOR?

18:11.675 --> 18:13.343
IF I CAN.

18:13.510 --> 18:15.804
YOU KNOW, THERE'S
SOME PEOPLE AROUND HERE
WOULDN'T BE TOO HAPPY

18:15.971 --> 18:18.390
TO FIND OUT
I'M NURSING A WOLF
BACK TO HEALTH HERE.

18:18.557 --> 18:20.726
YOU MAY BE
UNDERSTATING
THE CASE, JONATHAN,

18:20.893 --> 18:23.103
BUT DON'T WORRY.
I CAN KEEP
A SECRET, TOO.

18:23.270 --> 18:24.897
THANKS, DOC.

18:33.781 --> 18:36.200
[HAMMERING]

18:39.578 --> 18:42.414
LAURA INGALLS,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
UP THERE?

18:42.581 --> 18:43.874
WHAT DOES IT LOOK
LIKE I'M DOING?

18:44.041 --> 18:45.542
BUILDING
A TREE HOUSE!

18:45.709 --> 18:47.085
UH-HUH.

18:47.252 --> 18:48.754
YOU COME DOWN HERE
THIS MINUTE AND GET
YOURSELF OFF TO SCHOOL!

18:48.921 --> 18:50.339
[MIMICKING MARY]
YOU COME DOWN HERE
THIS MINUTE--

18:50.506 --> 18:51.465
LAURA!

18:51.632 --> 18:52.841
I'M COMING.
I'M COMING!

18:53.008 --> 18:54.426
DID YOU FINISH
ALL YOUR HOMEWORK?

18:54.593 --> 18:58.222
YES, AND I WASHED
BEHIND MY EARS, TOO.

19:00.015 --> 19:01.600
WHAT'S THIS TREE
HOUSE ALL ABOUT?

19:01.767 --> 19:03.560
IT'S ABOUT GETTING
AWAY FROM YOU

19:03.727 --> 19:05.729
AND HAVING A LITTLE
PEACE AND QUIET!

19:13.445 --> 19:14.822
I JUST CAN'T
BELIEVE IT!

19:14.988 --> 19:17.783
NEITHER COULD I
WHEN MY PA FIRST
TOLD ME.

19:17.950 --> 19:20.536
WOLVES--WE WERE
PLAYING WITH WOLVES!

19:20.702 --> 19:22.579
WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO?

19:22.746 --> 19:23.831
KEEP THEM.

19:23.997 --> 19:25.916
DOC BAKER CAME OVER
AND FIXED UP
HER LEG.

19:26.083 --> 19:27.459
HE SAYS
SHE'LL BE OK.

19:27.626 --> 19:28.919
IS YOUR PA
GOING TO LET YOU
KEEP THEM?

19:29.086 --> 19:30.462
YEP. HE PUT
A MUZZLE ON

19:30.629 --> 19:32.631
UNTIL SHE GETS
TO KNOW US BETTER,
THOUGH.

19:32.798 --> 19:33.799
HI.

19:33.966 --> 19:35.217
HI.

19:35.384 --> 19:36.677
HI.

19:38.095 --> 19:39.638
WHAT'S
THE BIG SECRET?

19:39.805 --> 19:40.973
THERE'S NO SECRET.

19:41.139 --> 19:42.516
NO SECRET.

19:42.683 --> 19:44.476
THEN I GUESS
NO ONE'S INTERESTED
IN THESE PENNY CANDIES.

19:44.643 --> 19:46.436
I WAS GOING TO
GIVE YOU SOME,

19:46.603 --> 19:49.314
BUT IF YOU DON'T
WANT TO BE FRIENDS...

19:50.816 --> 19:52.651
WE'RE JUST TALKING.

19:52.818 --> 19:54.611
I WAS JUST
TELLING ANDREW

19:54.778 --> 19:56.363
ABOUT THIS TREE HOUSE
I'M MAKING.

19:56.530 --> 19:57.698
YEAH, A TREE HOUSE.

19:57.865 --> 20:00.993
OK, HAVE
YOUR LITTLE SECRETS.

20:02.244 --> 20:05.747
NELLIE...PROMISE
NOT TO TELL ANYBODY?

20:05.914 --> 20:07.207
ANDY!

20:07.374 --> 20:08.542
PROMISE.

20:08.709 --> 20:10.544
I MEAN NO MATTER WHAT,
YOU WON'T TELL ANYBODY.

20:10.711 --> 20:12.713
CROSS MY HEART.

20:12.880 --> 20:14.631
YOU BETTER NOT.

20:14.798 --> 20:16.341
ME AND LAURA FOUND
A WOLF IN A TRAP,

20:16.508 --> 20:19.970
AND WE GOT HER FREE.
THEN WE BROUGHT HER
AND HER PUPS TO MY BARN.

20:20.137 --> 20:22.139
DOC BAKER CAME
AND FIXED UP HER LEG.

20:22.306 --> 20:24.182
YOU HAVE WOLVES
IN YOUR BARN?

20:24.349 --> 20:25.726
YEP.

20:25.893 --> 20:27.060
HOW INTERESTING.

20:27.227 --> 20:29.021
NOW HOW ABOUT
OUR CANDY?

20:29.187 --> 20:31.023
ALL RIGHT,
BUT JUST FOR YOU.

20:31.189 --> 20:32.524
LAURA DIDN'T
TELL ME ANYTHING.

20:32.691 --> 20:34.109
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

20:34.276 --> 20:36.403
WELL, BACK TO CLASS.

20:39.364 --> 20:40.616
WHERE IS SHE GOING?

20:40.782 --> 20:43.702
TO KEEP HER PROMISE
NOT TO TELL ANYONE.

20:43.869 --> 20:45.704
BUT SHE CROSSED
HER HEART.

20:45.871 --> 20:47.414
SHE HASN'T GOT ONE.

20:48.540 --> 20:50.542
ALL RIGHT, DOCTOR,
HERE YOU ARE.

20:50.709 --> 20:51.835
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

20:52.002 --> 20:53.712
IT'S ALWAYS
A PLEASURE
TO SERVE YOU.

20:53.879 --> 20:55.714
ALWAYS NICE TO HEAR,
MRS. OLESON.
GOOD DAY.

20:55.881 --> 20:56.757
GOOD DAY.

20:56.924 --> 20:58.050
Nellie: MOTHER!

20:58.216 --> 20:59.676
LAND'S SAKE, CHILD,
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

20:59.843 --> 21:01.470
I HEARD ANDREW
AND LAURA TALKING.

21:01.637 --> 21:05.057
THEY'RE KEEPING WOLVES
IN ANDREW'S BARN--
3 OF THEM.

21:05.223 --> 21:07.017
OH, DON'T BE
SILLY, MY DEAR.

21:07.184 --> 21:09.519
PEOPLE JUST
DON'T KEEP
A PACK OF WOLVES

21:09.686 --> 21:10.687
IN THEIR BARN.

21:10.854 --> 21:12.397
NOW, YOU RUN ALONG
BACK TO SCHOOL,

21:12.564 --> 21:14.858
AND DON'T YOU COME
HOME WITH ANY MORE
TALL TALES.

21:15.025 --> 21:17.277
IT'S TRUE.
ASK HIM. HE KNOWS.

21:17.444 --> 21:20.072
IS IT TRUE,
DOCTOR?

21:21.073 --> 21:22.574
I'M AFRAID IT IS.

21:22.741 --> 21:24.743
WELL, I CAN'T
BELIEVE IT!

21:24.910 --> 21:26.995
WE'VE GOT TO DO
SOMETHING!

21:27.162 --> 21:29.581
WHOA. HOLD ON THERE.

21:29.748 --> 21:33.168
GARVEY'S GOT
THE MOTHER WOLF MUZZLED.
THERE'S NO DANGER.

21:33.335 --> 21:35.253
BESIDES, THERE ISN'T
A MAN IN THE COUNTY,

21:35.420 --> 21:36.630
MUCH LESS THE WHOLE
TERRITORY,

21:36.797 --> 21:39.216
KNOWS AS MUCH
ABOUT WILD ANIMALS
AND THEIR WAYS

21:39.383 --> 21:41.301
AS JONATHAN GARVEY.
HE CAN HANDLE IT.

21:41.468 --> 21:43.512
WELL, I AM SHOCKED

21:43.679 --> 21:45.931
THAT YOU WOULD BE
A PARTY TO SUCH
A THING!

21:46.098 --> 21:48.225
WHAT ARE YOU?
A DOCTOR
OR A VETERINARIAN?

21:48.392 --> 21:51.603
YOU KNOW, MRS. OLESON,
LOOKING AT SOME
OF MY PATIENTS,

21:51.770 --> 21:53.271
I GET A LITTLE
CONFUSED MYSELF.

21:53.438 --> 21:54.856
GOOD DAY.

21:55.023 --> 21:59.778
NELLIE, I WANT YOU
TO RUN AN ERRAND FOR ME
TODAY AFTER SCHOOL.

21:59.945 --> 22:00.862
I WANT TO PLAY
AFTER SCHOOL.

22:01.029 --> 22:01.989
NOT TODAY!

22:02.155 --> 22:03.198
NOW, I WANT YOU
TO TAKE A MESSAGE

22:03.365 --> 22:05.450
OVER TO JUDD LARABEE'S
PLACE.

22:05.617 --> 22:06.493
YES, MOTHER.

22:06.660 --> 22:08.078
NOW, RUN ALONG!

22:09.621 --> 22:11.957
AH! ANOTHER
BEAUTIFUL DAY.

22:12.124 --> 22:15.961
YEP. THEY JUST
KEEP ON A-COMIN'.

22:16.128 --> 22:20.716
GOOD THAT CHARLES AND CAROLINE
HAVE THIS KIND OF WEATHER
FOR THEIR TRIP.

22:20.882 --> 22:23.885
YEAH. LOOKED IN ON THE GIRLS
THE OTHER DAY.

22:24.052 --> 22:29.558
THEY SEEMED TO BE DOING
PRETTY GOOD WITH...
WITHOUT THEIR MA AND PA.

22:29.725 --> 22:32.728
YOU KNOW, JACKSON
DROPPED IN A WHILE AGO,

22:32.894 --> 22:35.814
AND THE WOLVES BROUGHT DOWN
ONE OF HIS COWS.

22:35.981 --> 22:40.485
A COW. AND JUST LEFT IT
THERE FOR THE VULTURES
AND THE MAGGOTS.

22:40.652 --> 22:42.154
THEY DIDN'T EAT IT?
NO.

22:43.697 --> 22:46.158
THAT DON'T FIGURE.
THAT JUST DON'T FIGURE.

22:46.324 --> 22:50.328
HEAR ABOUT THEM WOLVES
KILLING HIS STOCK AND
JUST LETTING THEM LAY.

22:50.495 --> 22:51.747
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

22:51.913 --> 22:55.792
WELL, I'VE BEEN AROUND THEM
WOLVES BEFORE,

22:55.959 --> 22:58.003
AND THEY ONLY KILL
ENOUGH TO EAT.

22:58.170 --> 23:02.841
I CAN'T IMAGINE THEM ANIMALS
KILLING FOR THE SAKE
OF KILLING.

23:03.008 --> 23:04.885
WELL, I CAN'T ANSWER THAT.

23:05.052 --> 23:06.678
BUT I TELL YOU ONE THING,

23:06.845 --> 23:11.058
WHEN FOLKS GET DONE,
THERE WON'T BE A WOLF
LEFT ALIVE IN THESE PARTS.

23:11.224 --> 23:13.185
TIME TO GET BACK TO WORK.

23:21.193 --> 23:22.611
THEY'RE SO CUTE.

23:22.778 --> 23:24.905
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY EVERYBODY
HATES THEM.

23:25.072 --> 23:28.784
I USED TO,
ESPECIALLY AFTER I HEARD
<i>LITTLE RED RIDING HOOD.</i>

23:28.950 --> 23:31.912
YOU MEAN, "ALL
THE BETTER TO EAT
YOU WITH, MY DEAR!"

23:32.079 --> 23:32.996
YEAH. HA HA!

23:33.163 --> 23:34.456
YOU KNOW,
THOSE KIDS' STORIES,

23:34.623 --> 23:36.833
I GOT A FEELING
THAT GROWNUPS
MADE THEM UP.

23:37.000 --> 23:38.418
Laura: YOU'RE
PROBABLY RIGHT.

23:38.585 --> 23:41.046
SOMETIMES I CAN'T
FIGURE GROWNUPS OUT.

23:41.213 --> 23:42.881
SOMETIMES
I CAN'T EITHER.

23:43.048 --> 23:45.884
HI, PA. WE'RE TRYING
TO GIVE THEM NAMES.

23:46.051 --> 23:47.928
WHAT DO YOU THINK
ABOUT JONAH?

23:48.095 --> 23:49.221
HOLD ON NOW, SON.

23:49.387 --> 23:51.723
THAT'S A WOLF
YOU GOT THERE,
NOT A WHALE.

23:51.890 --> 23:55.227
BESIDES, I AIN'T SO SURE
YOU SHOULD BE NAMING
THEM CRITTERS.

23:55.393 --> 23:56.728
WHY?

23:56.895 --> 24:00.565
WELL, 'CAUSE
NAMES IS FOR PETS,
AND THEY AIN'T PETS.

24:00.732 --> 24:01.900
PA!

24:02.067 --> 24:03.193
NOW, HOLD ON
A SECOND.

24:03.360 --> 24:05.862
PETS IS A VERY SPECIAL
KIND OF THING.

24:06.029 --> 24:08.156
YOU KNOW, DOGS AND CATS
AND LIKE THAT,

24:08.323 --> 24:10.117
THEY GET
REAL CLOSE TO US.

24:10.283 --> 24:11.743
THEY GET TO BE
OUR FRIENDS.

24:11.910 --> 24:14.746
THEY LOVE US,
AND WE LOVE THEM.

24:14.913 --> 24:16.540
AND THAT'S THE WAY
IT IS WITH ANIMALS
LIKE THAT

24:16.706 --> 24:19.126
'CAUSE GOD MADE THEM
TO BE WITH PEOPLE.

24:19.292 --> 24:21.169
BUT SOME ANIMALS
HE MADE TO BE WILD.

24:21.336 --> 24:24.089
BUT THEY'RE
NOT WILD.
LOOK AT THEM!

24:24.256 --> 24:26.716
I'D TAKE REAL GOOD
CARE OF THEM.

24:26.883 --> 24:31.054
I KNOW YOU WOULD,
AND YOU'D TRAIN THEM,
AND YOU'D LOVE THEM,

24:31.221 --> 24:33.056
AND YOU'D PROBABLY
GET ALONG,

24:33.223 --> 24:35.016
BUT THEY WOULDN'T
REALLY BE HAPPY.

24:35.183 --> 24:38.311
THEY'D ALWAYS BE THINKING
ABOUT BEING FREE.

24:39.437 --> 24:41.690
YOU KNOW,
ONE TIME IN CHICAGO,

24:41.857 --> 24:45.068
I SAW A LADY
WITH A LION ON A LEASH.

24:45.235 --> 24:46.403
A LION?

24:46.570 --> 24:47.904
IN THE STREET?

24:48.071 --> 24:49.739
JUST AS PLAIN AS DAY.

24:49.906 --> 24:52.033
SHE WAS A-PARADING
UP AND DOWN,

24:52.200 --> 24:54.953
AND THAT LION
WAS GOING ALONG
RIGHT WITH HER

24:55.120 --> 24:56.872
AND LISTENING
TO HER.

24:58.290 --> 25:00.917
BUT YOU KNOW,
THERE WAS A...

25:01.084 --> 25:05.714
THERE WAS A LOOK
ON THAT LION'S FACE
THAT SAID, "I AIN'T HAPPY.

25:05.881 --> 25:10.135
"I WANT TO BE OUT
IN THE JUNGLE
WITH THE OTHER LIONS.

25:10.302 --> 25:13.555
I WANT TO BE ABLE
TO LET OUT A BIG ROAR."

25:15.056 --> 25:16.641
"I WANT TO BE FREE."

25:16.808 --> 25:18.560
[PUPS WHIMPERING]

25:22.939 --> 25:26.067
I THINK
WE OUGHT TO
LET THE WOLVES GO

25:26.234 --> 25:27.986
SO THEY CAN ROAR.

25:29.988 --> 25:31.072
GOOD IDEA.

25:31.239 --> 25:33.074
NOW, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT WE'LL DO.

25:33.241 --> 25:35.619
WE'LL KEEP THEM HERE
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS

25:35.785 --> 25:37.329
TILL THE MAMA'S
GOOD AND HEALED.

25:37.495 --> 25:40.207
AND THEN THE TWO OF YOU
CAN TAKE THEM OUT
INTO THE WOODS

25:40.373 --> 25:42.125
AND SET THEM FREE.

25:43.418 --> 25:45.337
AGREED.

25:51.843 --> 25:53.970
[HAMMERING]

25:58.934 --> 26:01.561
WELL, HOW DOES IT LOOK,
BANDIT?

26:01.728 --> 26:02.979
[RUFF RUFF]

26:03.146 --> 26:05.857
I AGREE...

26:06.024 --> 26:08.526
BUT WE NEED
SOMETHING.

26:10.362 --> 26:13.198
ALL THIS CLIMBING
UP AND DOWN

26:13.365 --> 26:15.533
IS GETTING
A LITTLE ROUGH.

26:16.868 --> 26:20.372
HEY, I KNOW
WHAT WE CAN GET.
COME ON, BANDIT.

26:26.127 --> 26:27.879
LAURA!

26:28.046 --> 26:29.881
LAURA INGALLS!

26:31.216 --> 26:33.051
LAURA, WHERE ARE YOU?

26:33.218 --> 26:35.595
I'M RIGHT HERE,
MASTER!

26:35.762 --> 26:37.264
TIME TO EAT.

26:37.430 --> 26:40.183
EAT? THAT STUFF
YOU MAKE IS AWFUL!

26:40.350 --> 26:44.020
I'M RUNNING OUT
OF PATIENCE.

26:44.187 --> 26:45.939
ALL RIGHT.
I'LL BE IN
IN A MINUTE.

26:46.106 --> 26:48.483
WHAT ARE YOU AND ANDY
GOING TO DO ABOUT
YOUR WOLVES?

26:48.650 --> 26:51.403
I HEARD A COW WAS KILLED
JUST A FEW MILES FROM TOWN.

26:51.569 --> 26:52.946
THAT WASN'T
<i>OUR</i> WOLVES.

26:53.113 --> 26:54.906
I KNOW.
I'M JUST ASKING.

26:55.073 --> 26:57.534
WE'RE GOING TO
SET THEM FREE--
PROBABLY TOMORROW.

26:57.701 --> 26:59.911
I'LL BE IN
IN A MINUTE.

27:00.078 --> 27:01.788
YOU BETTER BE.

27:07.377 --> 27:09.087
[GRUNTING]

27:15.927 --> 27:17.470
OOPS. LOOK OUT,
BANDIT.

27:18.930 --> 27:21.599
THIS WILL DO IT.
COME ON, BOY!

27:45.290 --> 27:48.126
WANT TO TALK
TO YOU, GARVEY.

27:48.293 --> 27:50.086
ALL RIGHT.
WHAT IS IT?

27:50.253 --> 27:52.714
UNDERSTAND YOU GOT
A COUPLE OF WOLVES

27:52.881 --> 27:54.799
KIND OF MOVED IN
WITH YOU.

27:54.966 --> 27:56.176
SO?

27:56.343 --> 27:57.635
I WANT 'EM.

27:57.802 --> 28:00.638
LOOK, IT AIN'T NONE
OF YOUR AFFAIR.

28:00.805 --> 28:03.850
JUST GO ABOUT WHAT
YOU COME TO TOWN TO DO

28:04.017 --> 28:05.518
AND LEAVE ME BE.

28:10.315 --> 28:13.526
THIS IS WHAT
I COME TO TOWN FOR.

28:18.907 --> 28:21.326
I GOT DEAD LIVESTOCK.
YOU GOT LIVE WOLVES.

28:21.493 --> 28:23.119
NOW, THERE'S
SOMETHING ABOUT THAT

28:23.286 --> 28:25.163
THAT JUST AIN'T
RIGHT TO ME.

28:26.331 --> 28:28.541
I'M SORRY
ABOUT THIS, BUT...

28:29.834 --> 28:31.669
DON'T LOOK LIKE
A WOLF KILL TO ME.

28:31.836 --> 28:33.505
JUST DON'T LOOK
LIKE A WOLF KILL.

28:33.671 --> 28:35.090
BESIDES,
EVEN IF IT IS,

28:35.256 --> 28:36.925
ALL I GOT'S
A WOUNDED MOTHER

28:37.092 --> 28:38.301
AND A COUPLE
OF PUPS.

28:38.468 --> 28:40.178
HOW MUCH DAMAGE
CAN THEY DO?

28:40.345 --> 28:42.180
WOUNDS HEAL.
PUPS GROW UP.

28:42.347 --> 28:44.599
NOW, I WANT
THEM WOLVES DEAD.

28:44.766 --> 28:47.894
IF YOU DON'T DO IT,
I WILL.

28:48.853 --> 28:51.189
NOW, YOU STAY AWAY
FROM THEM WOLVES.

28:51.356 --> 28:53.024
YOU STAY OFF
OF MY PROPERTY,

28:53.191 --> 28:58.530
AND YOU STAY AS
FAR AWAY FROM ME
AS YOU POSSIBLY CAN.

28:59.531 --> 29:01.366
THE MATTER
IS CLOSED.

29:14.879 --> 29:17.006
[BARKING]

29:29.561 --> 29:32.063
Mrs. Oleson:
SO I'LL SPREAD
THE WORD

29:32.230 --> 29:34.023
TO ANY OF THE MEN
WHO HAPPEN
TO COME AROUND.

29:34.190 --> 29:35.984
TELL THEM TO MEET
AT MY PLACE TONIGHT.

29:36.151 --> 29:38.194
WE'LL HEAD OVER
TO GARVEY'S FROM THERE.

29:38.361 --> 29:40.155
I'LL DO WHATEVER
I CAN TO HELP.

29:40.321 --> 29:42.240
APPRECIATE IT.
THANKS FOR SENDING
THE MESSAGE.

29:42.407 --> 29:43.700
OH, NOW, BE CAREFUL

29:43.867 --> 29:46.786
BECAUSE THAT MR. GARVEY
CAN BE VERY STUBBORN.

29:46.953 --> 29:48.163
I WANT
THEM WOLVES DEAD,

29:48.329 --> 29:50.623
AND I'M GOING TO SEE TO IT
THAT THEY ARE.

29:50.790 --> 29:54.419
IF HE GETS STUBBORN,
HE'S GOING TO BE HEADED
FOR A HEAP OF TROUBLE.

29:54.586 --> 29:56.588
GOOD DAY.
GOOD DAY.

30:10.894 --> 30:12.645
WE'RE GOING
FOR A RIDE.

30:12.812 --> 30:15.273
NOTHING'S GOING TO
HAPPEN--NOTHING BAD.

30:15.440 --> 30:17.108
I'LL MAKE SURE
OF THAT.

30:17.275 --> 30:18.985
[PUPS WHIMPERING]

30:34.626 --> 30:37.378
HEY, LAURA!

30:37.545 --> 30:39.631
HI, ANDY!

30:47.263 --> 30:49.057
HAD TO BRING
THE WOLVES.

30:49.224 --> 30:50.183
HOW COME?

30:50.350 --> 30:51.768
A MAN--HE'S
GONNA KILL THEM.

30:51.935 --> 30:52.810
I HEARD HIM TALKING.

30:52.977 --> 30:53.770
WHO WAS HE?

30:53.937 --> 30:54.729
I DON'T KNOW,

30:54.896 --> 30:55.897
BUT HE SOUNDED
AWFUL MEAN.

30:56.064 --> 30:58.316
I'LL HAVE TO HIDE THEM
OUT HERE, OK?

30:58.483 --> 31:00.026
DID YOU TELL
YOUR PA?

31:00.193 --> 31:02.320
I COULDN'T. THEY'RE ANGRY
AT HIM, TOO...

31:02.487 --> 31:05.073
AND I'M SCARED FOR HIM.
I JUST FIGURED OUT

31:05.240 --> 31:06.908
THAT I BETTER GET THEM
OUT OF THERE.

31:07.075 --> 31:09.202
OK, WE'LL KEEP THEM
IN MY BARN,

31:09.369 --> 31:10.328
BUT DON'T TELL MARY.

31:10.495 --> 31:11.663
WHY?

31:11.829 --> 31:13.331
SHE'LL FIGURE OUT
SOME RULE I'M BREAKING

31:13.498 --> 31:14.332
BY KEEPING THEM HERE.

31:14.499 --> 31:16.167
LET'S GO. COME ON.

31:21.839 --> 31:23.049
WHERE'S YOUR SISTER?

31:23.216 --> 31:24.217
I DON'T KNOW.

31:24.384 --> 31:25.802
SHE MUST BE UP
IN HER TREE HOUSE.

31:25.969 --> 31:27.887
I TOLD HER TO BE IN
BY SUPPERTIME.

31:28.054 --> 31:30.223
I'LL GET HER.
COME ON, BANDIT!

31:30.390 --> 31:31.975
TELL HER TO HURRY!

31:33.518 --> 31:35.853
LAURA,
MARY WANTS YOU!

31:37.939 --> 31:39.691
[DOGS BARKING]

31:45.780 --> 31:47.699
[DOGS BARKING]

32:00.336 --> 32:02.338
CARRIE, COME ON!
HURRY!

32:04.716 --> 32:06.384
COME ON.

32:11.180 --> 32:12.390
WHAT IS IT?

32:12.557 --> 32:13.766
HELP ME GET THIS
BOLTED.

32:14.726 --> 32:15.893
Laura:
WHAT IS IT?

32:16.060 --> 32:17.312
WHAT'S OUT THERE?

32:17.478 --> 32:19.731
SOME KIND OF DOGS
GONE CRAZY.
GET THE WINDOW.

32:26.529 --> 32:28.239
WE'RE SAFE NOW.

32:28.406 --> 32:31.117
THERE'S NO WAY
THEY'LL GET IN.

32:41.711 --> 32:44.130
[CHICKENS SQUAWKING]

32:44.297 --> 32:46.549
[COWS BELLOWING]

33:23.127 --> 33:25.338
THEY'LL PROBABLY
GO NOW.

33:27.674 --> 33:29.008
I'M SCARED.

33:29.175 --> 33:30.802
ME, TOO.

33:43.564 --> 33:45.942
IT'S ALL RIGHT TO BE
A LITTLE SCARED.

33:47.360 --> 33:49.612
NOTHING'S GOING TO
HAPPEN TO US.

33:51.197 --> 33:52.657
WE'RE SAFE IN HERE.

33:52.824 --> 33:54.742
[DOG BARKS AND
SNARLS LOUDLY]

33:58.830 --> 33:59.997
COME ON, LET'S SING.

34:00.164 --> 34:01.416
WHAT?

34:01.582 --> 34:03.668
Mary: YOU KNOW,
MA SOMETIMES SINGS TO US

34:03.835 --> 34:05.420
WHEN WE DON'T FEEL
TOO GOOD,

34:05.586 --> 34:07.547
AND RIGHT NOW
I DON'T FEEL TOO GOOD.

34:07.714 --> 34:09.841
ME, NEITHER.

34:11.926 --> 34:13.094
Mary: HOW ABOUT...

34:13.261 --> 34:14.595
<i>OH! SUSANNA.</i>

34:15.596 --> 34:16.973
<i>OH! SUSANNA.</i>

34:17.140 --> 34:18.599
EVERYBODY READY?

34:18.766 --> 34:20.101
MM-HMM.

34:20.268 --> 34:24.105
All: ♪ OH, I COME
FROM ALABAMA ♪

34:24.272 --> 34:26.357
♪ WITH MY BANJO
ON MY KNEE ♪

34:26.524 --> 34:32.405
♪ I'M GOIN' TO LOUISIANA,
MY SUSANNA FOR TO SEE ♪

34:32.572 --> 34:38.369
♪ OH! SUSANNA,
OH, DON'T YOU CRY FOR ME ♪

34:38.536 --> 34:43.750
♪ FOR I COME FROM ALABAMA
WITH MY BANJO ON MY KNEE ♪

34:43.916 --> 34:47.378
♪ IT RAINED ALL NIGHT
THE DAY I LEFT ♪

34:47.545 --> 34:49.922
♪ THE WEATHER,
IT WAS DRY ♪

34:50.089 --> 34:52.717
♪ THE SUN SO HOT
I FROZE TO DEATH ♪

34:52.884 --> 34:55.887
♪ SUSANNA,
DON'T YOU CRY... ♪

35:48.773 --> 35:51.609
HOW LONG
HAS IT BEEN?

35:51.776 --> 35:53.444
COUPLE HOURS.

35:53.611 --> 35:55.988
I'M HUNGRY.
CAN'T WE GO IN THE HOUSE?

35:56.155 --> 35:57.615
NOT YET.

35:57.782 --> 36:00.535
WELL, THEY SHOULD BE
GONE BY NOW.

36:00.701 --> 36:02.620
WELL,
IT'S TOO DARK
OUTSIDE TO TELL.

36:02.787 --> 36:05.540
WE CAN'T TAKE
A CHANCE.

36:05.706 --> 36:06.874
[RUSTLING]

36:07.041 --> 36:08.668
WHAT WAS THAT?

36:08.835 --> 36:10.002
WHAT?

36:10.169 --> 36:11.963
LISTEN.

36:19.846 --> 36:22.014
[SCRATCHING]

36:30.147 --> 36:31.566
WHAT IS IT?

36:31.732 --> 36:33.192
I DON'T KNOW.

36:37.321 --> 36:39.490
[BARKING AND GROWLING]

36:43.911 --> 36:45.538
THEY'RE DIGGING
UNDER THE WALL!

36:45.705 --> 36:47.582
EVERYBODY
UP IN THE HAYLOFT!

36:47.748 --> 36:48.875
WHERE'S THE LADDER?

36:49.041 --> 36:51.544
THE LADDER--I TOOK IT
TO MY TREE HOUSE.

36:51.711 --> 36:53.713
I NEEDED IT
TO CLIMB UP.

36:56.424 --> 36:58.342
ON THE TABLE!
HURRY!

37:09.812 --> 37:12.148
COME ON, HURRY!

37:13.107 --> 37:15.693
Mary: COME ON,
CARRIE.

37:16.736 --> 37:19.238
THERE.
GET OVER THERE.

37:29.832 --> 37:31.709
WE FORGOT THE WOLF
AND THE PUPS!

37:31.876 --> 37:33.002
WE HAVEN'T GOT TIME.

37:33.169 --> 37:35.171
GET OVER THERE
WITH CARRIE.
COME ON, HURRY!

37:35.338 --> 37:36.714
THEY'RE IN HERE.
I'LL GET THEM.

37:36.881 --> 37:38.215
Mary:
THERE'S NO TIME!

37:42.887 --> 37:44.764
HURRY. GET UP HERE.

37:44.931 --> 37:46.349
[PUPS WHIMPERING]

37:46.515 --> 37:48.768
WAIT.
WHERE'S BANDIT?

37:48.935 --> 37:49.894
I'LL GET HIM.

37:50.061 --> 37:51.479
COME ON!
COME ON, BANDIT!

37:51.646 --> 37:54.690
COME ON, BANDIT.
COME ON! COME ON! COME ON!

38:02.907 --> 38:04.200
ANDY, HURRY!

38:20.007 --> 38:21.550
COME ON.

38:31.811 --> 38:33.980
[DOGS AND WOLF SNARLING]

38:38.943 --> 38:41.070
[DOGS BARKING]

38:49.787 --> 38:52.331
SHH. SHH.
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

38:52.498 --> 38:54.291
IT'S GOING TO BE
ALL RIGHT.

38:54.458 --> 38:56.460
Andy: I SURE WISH
MY PA WOULD COME.

38:56.627 --> 38:59.130
I WAS SURE HE'D
COME LOOKING FOR ME.

39:00.965 --> 39:03.300
WHAT IF
NO ONE COMES?

39:04.969 --> 39:07.596
BANDIT KNOWS THE WAY
TO ANDY'S HOUSE.

39:08.556 --> 39:10.516
Mary: MAYBE HE COULD
GET MR. GARVEY.

39:10.683 --> 39:12.435
NO. THOSE DOGS
WILL GET HIM.

39:12.601 --> 39:14.478
LAURA,
WE HAVE TO TRY IT.

39:17.064 --> 39:18.441
OK.

39:25.406 --> 39:27.867
YOU'VE GOT TO
DO THIS, BANDIT--

39:28.034 --> 39:29.326
YOU GOT TO.

39:29.493 --> 39:31.287
GO GET MR. GARVEY

39:31.454 --> 39:33.330
AND MAKE HIM
COME WITH YOU.

39:33.497 --> 39:35.624
PLEASE, BANDIT.

39:37.376 --> 39:39.795
IT'S ALL CLEAR,
LAURA. COME ON.

39:42.673 --> 39:44.300
BE CAREFUL, BANDIT.

39:54.226 --> 39:55.978
[DOG GROWLING]

39:57.104 --> 39:58.898
[BARKING]

40:40.064 --> 40:41.524
[WHIMPER]

41:11.679 --> 41:15.182
Mrs. Garvey:
JONATHAN, YOU'RE LATE.

41:15.349 --> 41:16.684
THEM WOLVES
IS GONE.

41:16.851 --> 41:17.893
WHERE'S ANDREW?

41:18.060 --> 41:19.520
ANDY? I THOUGHT
HE WAS WITH YOU.

41:19.687 --> 41:21.105
HE SAID HE WAS GOING TO
MEET YOU AFTER SCHOOL.

41:21.272 --> 41:24.108
I AIN'T SEEN HIM.
HAS LARABEE BEEN AROUND?

41:24.275 --> 41:25.734
NO.

41:25.901 --> 41:28.070
HAS ANYBODY BEEN AROUND
HERE, ANY STRANGERS?

41:28.237 --> 41:29.280
NO.

41:29.446 --> 41:31.949
I DON'T THINK SO.
I DIDN'T SEE ANYONE.

41:32.116 --> 41:33.325
[BANDIT WHIMPERING]

41:33.492 --> 41:34.827
Alice:
IT'S LAURA'S DOG.

41:34.994 --> 41:38.414
EASY, BOY, EASY.
I AIN'T GONNA
HURT YOU, NOW.

41:38.581 --> 41:40.583
YOU'VE BEEN BIT...

41:40.749 --> 41:42.626
BUT IT AIN'T
TOO BAD.

41:42.793 --> 41:44.128
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

41:44.295 --> 41:45.796
HE--HE'S HURT.

41:45.963 --> 41:47.715
WHY DID HE
COME HERE?

41:47.882 --> 41:49.300
TROUBLE
AT THE INGALLS'!

41:49.466 --> 41:51.552
DO YOU THINK
THE WOLF HURT HIM?

41:51.719 --> 41:53.804
I PRAY TO GOD
THAT'S ALL SHE HURT.

41:53.971 --> 41:57.016
WHY DID I EVER
LET THAT BOY BRING
THAT ANIMAL IN HERE?

41:57.183 --> 42:00.186
YOU STAY HERE
IN CASE
HE COMES HOME.

42:05.149 --> 42:08.527
WE CAME ABOUT THAT MATTER
YOU AND ME DISCUSSED.

42:08.694 --> 42:09.486
NOT NOW.

42:09.653 --> 42:11.155
NOW'S AS GOOD
A TIME AS ANY.

42:11.322 --> 42:12.281
WHERE'S THEM WOLVES?

42:12.448 --> 42:13.699
MY BOY AND 3 OTHERS
IS IN TROUBLE.

42:13.866 --> 42:14.992
WHAT KIND OF
TROUBLE?

42:15.159 --> 42:16.410
Jonathan:
I DON'T KNOW...

42:17.328 --> 42:18.996
BUT I'M GOING TO
FIND OUT.

42:19.163 --> 42:20.497
NOW,
YOU WANT TO RIDE

42:20.664 --> 42:21.999
ALONG WITH ME,
THAT'S FINE.

42:22.166 --> 42:23.876
IF NOT,
OUT OF MY WAY.

42:29.465 --> 42:31.508
[BARKING]

42:48.692 --> 42:51.362
[DOG SNARLING]

42:54.782 --> 42:57.243
[DOG WHIMPERING]

43:17.554 --> 43:18.806
[DOG GROWLING]

43:29.441 --> 43:30.901
[GUN COCKS AND FIRES]

43:31.068 --> 43:32.945
[GUNSHOTS]

43:35.155 --> 43:36.949
[BARKING FADING]

43:40.536 --> 43:42.413
[SHOOTING STOPS]

43:44.331 --> 43:45.749
EVERYONE ALL RIGHT?

43:45.916 --> 43:47.835
WE'RE FINE.

43:48.002 --> 43:49.461
[PANTING]

44:02.057 --> 44:04.852
SHE SAVED MY LIFE.

44:06.270 --> 44:09.064
THE MAMA WOLF
SAVED MY LIFE.

44:20.909 --> 44:22.453
[SOBBING]

44:39.345 --> 44:42.765
[PUPS WHIMPERING]

44:54.693 --> 44:55.986
I DON'T THINK
IT'S GOING TO WORK.

44:56.153 --> 44:57.821
[QUIETLY]
SHH. IT'S GOING TO WORK.

44:57.988 --> 44:59.865
YOU JUST GOT TO GIVE IT
A LITTLE TIME.

45:00.032 --> 45:02.618
THAT MAMA WOLF'S
BEING AWFUL CAREFUL.

45:05.579 --> 45:07.081
I STILL DON'T
UNDERSTAND...

45:07.247 --> 45:08.457
ABOUT THE DOGS.

45:08.624 --> 45:11.502
THAT'S KIND OF A HARD ONE
TO GET AHOLD OF,

45:11.668 --> 45:14.088
BUT I'LL WAGER YOU
THAT ALL THEM DOGS

45:14.254 --> 45:16.590
WAS ONCE GOOD FAMILY PETS,
JUST LIKE YOUR MUTT.

45:16.757 --> 45:19.176
THEN WHY DID THEY DO
WHAT THEY DID?

45:19.343 --> 45:20.469
WELL, BECAUSE...

45:20.636 --> 45:22.846
THEIR MASTERS JUST
GOT TIRED OF THEM.

45:23.013 --> 45:25.015
YOU KNOW HOW I TOLD YOU
THAT, UH...

45:25.182 --> 45:28.977
IT'S WRONG TO TAKE A WILD ANIMAL
AND MAKE A PET OUT OF IT?

45:29.144 --> 45:31.355
WELL, IT'S JUST AS BAD--
MAYBE WORSE--

45:31.522 --> 45:34.775
TO TAKE A PET
AND TURN IT INTO A WILD ANIMAL.

45:35.818 --> 45:37.277
BUT HOW?

45:37.444 --> 45:38.862
BY...

45:39.029 --> 45:40.531
NOT CARING,

45:40.697 --> 45:43.117
STOP LOVING THEM,
STOP FEEDING THEM,

45:43.283 --> 45:44.785
STOP TAKING CARE
OF THEM,

45:44.952 --> 45:47.413
THEN TURN THEM LOOSE
TO FEND FOR THEMSELVES.

45:47.579 --> 45:49.164
MR. GARVEY.

45:49.331 --> 45:50.874
[RUSTLING]

45:55.921 --> 45:57.423
COME ON, MAMA.

45:57.589 --> 45:59.341
[PUPS WHIMPERING]

46:14.440 --> 46:17.025
HOLD REAL STILL NOW.

46:17.192 --> 46:19.570
REAL STILL.

46:27.536 --> 46:30.873
COME ON, GET
THE OTHER BABY, MAMA.

46:32.166 --> 46:35.085
THERE SHE COMES.
EASY NOW.

47:15.417 --> 47:17.544
DO YOU THINK
THEY'LL BE HAPPY?

47:17.711 --> 47:20.380
OH, ABOUT AS HAPPY AS
TWO YOUNG CUBS

47:20.547 --> 47:22.090
IN A HONEY TREE.

47:22.257 --> 47:23.091
HA HA HA!

47:23.258 --> 47:24.301
NOW, COME ON.

47:24.468 --> 47:26.220
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE
REAL EASY, NOW,

47:26.386 --> 47:28.388
AND LEAVE THEM BE.

47:32.476 --> 47:34.520
SURE AM GOING
TO MISS THEM.

47:36.605 --> 47:38.607
ME, TOO.

47:40.400 --> 47:42.653
[QUIETLY]
HEY, YOU TWO,
GET A MOVE ON.

47:49.660 --> 47:51.620
NOW, I HEAR
OLD MAN STIMSON'S HOUND

47:51.787 --> 47:53.080
HAS GOT SOME NEW PUPS,

47:53.247 --> 47:55.332
AND IF WE'RE GONNA GET THERE
AND TAKE A LOOK AT THEM,

47:55.499 --> 47:56.833
WE'RE GOING TO
HAVE TO HURRY.

47:57.000 --> 47:58.252
YOU MEAN IT--A PUP?

47:58.418 --> 48:00.712
OF COURSE
I MEAN IT, NOW.
